Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, Egypt, March 4 (AFP)--Muslim militants shot 
and seriously wounded a German tourist Friday when they opened 
fire on a Nile cruise boat in southern Egypt, security sources 
said. 
  The tourist was taken to a hospital in the southern city of 
Asyut after he was shot while on the cruise near Abu Tij, some 
30 kilometres (18 miles) south of here, the sources said. The 
victim was not named. 
  There was no confirmation of the incident from the Interior 
Ministry or the German Embassy in Cairo. [passage omitted] 

